text: Georgy Ivanovich Gushchenko (Russian: Георгий Иванович Гущенко; born 2 March 1931) is a Russian rower who represented the Soviet Union. He competed at the 1952 Summer Olympics in Helsinki with the men's coxed four where they were eliminated in the semi-final repêchage. He competed at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne with the men's eight where they were eliminated in the semi-final. ==References== Category:1931 births Category:Living people Category:Soviet male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of the Soviet Union Category:Rowers at the 1952 Summer Olympics Category:Rowers at the 1956 Summer Olympics Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
